<font color="#FF0000">ROLL CALL 1ST PLATOON USMC</font><br>
<tt>Fri Nov 14 22:20:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Ira, didn't have to die, <br>
he was suppose to have been left in the rear, he was to short, was suppose to rotate out the very next day. The new 2nd looie kept him out in the field.<br><br>
We knew a battalion of gooks had been seen out there, by Charlie's ridge, and that we were being used as bait. Why else would a lone platoon be way out there all alone in the boonies. We had an air observer with us, they only came out with us when we were bait or with the whole company, but it was just us.<br>
 <br>
When Ira got hit, the 2nd Lt. wouldn't send up the gun team,  I wanted to go, boy, I wanted to go. But he wouldn't let me, Chief almost wasted the lieutenant right there and then.<br>
Ira didn't have to die. <br><br>
Then the Lt. called in artillery, out in the open rice paddies, almost on top of us, dumb, dumb, dumb, Lt.<br><br>
Almost shot the Lt. myself a couple of months later, but that New years Eve, Ira didn't have to die.<br><br>
1st Platoon, India Company 3/7, 1st Marine Division<br>
